.feature
  %h2 Beauty
  %p
    Sass does away with the unnecessary brackets and semicolons of CSS.
    Properties are nested beneath selectors,
    and each property gets its own line.

  %pre.sass
    :preserve
      h1
        height: 118px
        margin-top: 1em

      .tagline
        font-size: 26px
        text-align: right

  %pre.css
    :preserve
      h1 {
        height: 118px;
        margin-top: 1em;
      }

      .tagline {
        font-size: 26px;
        text-align: right;
      }
